      • is

        List<FilterExpression<T>> is(V value)
        Generates an expression to select all elements with the given attribute value. For example: filtering by "red" would select only those elements with "red" value.
        Parameters:
        value - the value to filter by
        Returns:
        a filter expression for the given value

      • isIn

        default List<FilterExpression<T>> isIn(Iterable<V> values)
        Generates an expression to select all elements with attributes matching any of the given values. For example: filtering by ["red", "blue"] would select only those elements with either "red" or "blue" value.

        Alias for containsAny(Iterable).

        Parameters:
        values - the values to filter by
        Returns:
        a filter expression for the given values
